i is a 1  ×  k matrix of variables representing characteristics of individual i as well as risk relating attitudes, β is a k  ×  1 vector of coefficients which has to be estimated and ε stands for the error term. What is known is the probability of an affirmative response to the payment question. The sequence of the yes (y) and no (n) answers is pictured by the following dummy variables:
